{"title_page": "Organisation for Marxist Unity \u2013 New Zealand", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\nThe '''Organisation for Marxist Unity''' (OMU) was founded in the 1975 as the '''Preparatory Committee for the Formation of the Communist Party of New Zealand (Marxist\u2013Leninist)''' by former members of the [[Communist Party of New Zealand]] (CPNZ) including Don Ross, Alec Ostler and Peter Manson. They were opposed to the CPNZ's break with the [[Communist Party of China]] after the death of Mao and continued to uphold China under [[Deng Xiaoping]] as a model socialist state.\n\nIn 1988 they changed the name of the group to the Organisation for Marxist Unity, and ceased production of their monthly newspaper in favour of the quarterly magazine ''Struggle''.  Since the mid-1990s the OMU has been in merger negotiations with the [[Communist Party of Aotearoa]], another more recent split from the CPNZ, although as of 2008 no merger had taken place.\n\nIn recent years members of the OMU have also been active in the group [[Campaign Against Foreign Control of Aotearoa]] (CAFCA).\n\n==References==\n<references />\n*Ron Smith, ''Working Class Son: My Fight against Capitalism and War: Memoirs of Ron Smith, a New Zealand Communist'': Self-published, 1994. {{ISBN|0-473-02909-X}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Organisation for Marxist Unity - New Zealand}}\n[[Category:Communist parties in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Maoist organizations]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1975]]\n\n\n{{NewZealand-org-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\nThe '''Organisation for Marxist Unity''' (OMU) was founded in the 1975 as the '''Preparatory Committee for the Formation of the Communist Party of New Zealand (Marxist\u2013Leninist)''', by former members of the [[Communist Party of New Zealand|CPNZ]] including Don Ross, Alec Ostler and Peter Manson. They were opposed to the CPNZ's break with the [[Communist Party of China]] after the death of Mao and continued to uphold China under [[Deng Xiaoping]] as a model socialist state.\n\nIn 1988 they changed the name of the group to the Organisation for Marxist Unity, and ceased production of their monthly newspaper in favour of the quarterly magazine ''Struggle''.  Since the mid-1990s the OMU has been in merger negotiations with the [[Communist Party of Aotearoa]], another more recent split from the CPNZ, although as of 2008 no merger had taken place.\n\nIn recent years members of the OMU have also been active in the group [[Campaign Against Foreign Control of Aotearoa]] (CAFCA).\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n*Ron Smith, ''Working class son: my fight against capitalism and war: memoirs of Ron Smith, a New Zealand communist'': self-published, 1994. {{ISBN|0-473-02909-X}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Organisation for Marxist Unity - New Zealand}}\n[[Category:Communist parties in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Maoist organizations]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1975]]\n\n\n{{NewZealand-org-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Nurg", "label": "safe", "comment": "c/e", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organisation_for_Marxist_Unity_%E2%80%93_New_Zealand"}
